claim.claim-text:
1. A small computer system interface (SCSI) driver circuit having a programmable slew rate, comprising:
N cascaded delay cells, each including:
a data bit input,
a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay cells, and
a delay time input that receives a programmable delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;

N predrivers that receive an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and that generate a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
N drivers that have inputs that receive predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predrivers;
an output port that communicates with outputs of said N drivers.

13. A method for operating a small computer system interface (SCSI) driver circuit having a programmable slew rate, comprising:
providing N cascaded delay cells each including a data bit input, a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay cells, and a delay time input;
programming a delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;
receiving an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and generating a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
coupling inputs of N drivers to predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predrivers; and
coupling an output port with outputs of said N drivers.

22. A small computer system interface (SCSI) driver circuit having a programmable slew rate, comprising:
N cascaded delay means for delaying, each including:
a data bit input,
a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay means, and
a delay time input that receives a programmable delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;

N predriving means for receiving an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and for generating a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
N driving means for driving that have inputs that receive predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predriving means;
an output port that communicates with outputs of said N driving means.

34. A driver circuit having a programmable slew rate, comprising:
N cascaded delay means for delaying, each including:
a data bit input,
a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay means, and
a delay time input that receives a programmable delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;

N predriving means for receiving an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and for generating a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
N driving means for driving that have inputs that receive predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predriving means;
an output port that communicates with outputs of said N driving means.

35. A driver circuit having a programmable slew rate, comprising:
N cascaded delay cells, each including:
a data bit input,
a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay cells, and
a delay time input that receives a programmable delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;
N predrivers that receive an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and that generate a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
N drivers that have inputs that receive predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predrivers;
an output port that communicates with outputs of said N drivers.

36. A method for operating a driver circuit having programmable slew rate, comprising:
providing N cascaded delay cells each including a data bit input, a delayed data bit output that communicates with said data bit input of an adjacent one of said N cascaded delay cells, and a delay time input;
programming a delay time value for setting a variable delay between receiving data at said data bit input and generating said delayed data bit output;
receiving an output enable signal, which is independent of said data bit input, and a corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs and generating a predriver output signal based on said output enable and said corresponding one of said N delayed data bit outputs;
coupling inputs of N drivers to predriver output signals from corresponding ones of said N predrivers; and
coupling an output port with outputs of said N drivers.
